WEBVTT

00:00:02.202 --> 00:00:06.139
♬ "Be brave and say you'll win"

00:00:06.139 --> 00:00:11.445
Three years have passed since Suzuko returned from Kagawa.

00:00:13.614 --> 00:00:18.485
The Umemaru Girls' Opera Company is centered around Suzuko's generation➡

00:00:18.485 --> 00:00:21.788
It is becoming more and more popular.

00:00:23.624 --> 00:00:33.300
♬～(applause)

00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:38.972
♬～(hand beat)

00:00:38.972 --> 00:00:47.314
(Suzuko) ♬ “I want to be held in your chest”

00:00:47.314 --> 00:00:54.988
♬ “Even the flowers are flaming red” (All members) ♬ “Cheerio”

00:00:54.988 --> 00:01:03.263
♬ “You look happy, but it’s embarrassing.”

00:01:03.263 --> 00:01:11.138
♬ “Step of Love, Dreamy Cheerio”

00:01:11.138 --> 00:01:19.279
♬～(cheers)

00:01:19.279 --> 00:01:22.950
♬～

00:01:22.950 --> 00:01:31.291
♬“One sincere heart, the end”

00:01:31.291 --> 00:01:38.966
♬ “Tightly tied chest string” (all) ♬ “Cheerio”

00:01:38.966 --> 00:01:47.307
♬ “You look happy, but it’s embarrassing.”

00:01:47.307 --> 00:01:55.182
♬ “Step of Love, Dreamy Cheerio”

00:01:55.182 --> 00:01:59.319
♬～(applause and cheers)

00:01:59.319 --> 00:02:05.592
♬～

00:02:05.592 --> 00:02:07.928
♬～

00:02:07.928 --> 00:02:14.267
♬ “What is this rhythm?”

00:02:14.267 --> 00:02:17.604
♬ "It's like weightlessness"

00:02:17.604 --> 00:02:20.941
♬ “Boogie woogie makes my heart feel lighter.”

00:02:20.941 --> 00:02:25.278
♬ "Flying in the sky"

00:02:25.278 --> 00:02:30.617
♬～

00:02:30.617 --> 00:02:33.520
♬ “Boogie Woogie Woogie Boogie Woogie Woogie”

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:36.490
♬ "Magic words"

00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:40.627
♬ “My body starts dancing naturally”

00:02:40.627 --> 00:02:43.296
♬ “Daba-doo-dida, it won’t stop”

00:02:43.296 --> 00:02:46.199
♬ “Boogie Woogie Woogie Boogie Woogie Woogie”

00:02:46.199 --> 00:02:49.169
♬ “Everyone is crazy about it”

00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:54.641
♬ “My heart is excited and excited”

00:02:54.641 --> 00:02:57.310
♬ “Dabadudidah, I love you”

00:02:57.310 --> 00:03:00.213
♬ “Boogie Woogie Woogie I love you (Boogie Woogie)”

00:03:00.213 --> 00:03:03.583
♬ “I’m so happy (I love you)”

00:03:03.583 --> 00:03:09.256
♬ “Let’s run, break out, sing and dance!”

00:03:09.256 --> 00:03:14.928
♬ “Let’s dance passionately!”

00:03:14.928 --> 00:03:18.398
♬～

00:03:18.398 --> 00:03:21.935
Then I apologize in advance. Excuse me. Take care when you return home.

00:03:21.935 --> 00:03:23.870
yes. see you tomorrow.

00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:28.275
Hasn't he been trained a lot? (Akiyama) Of course, but➡

00:03:28.275 --> 00:03:31.278
Thanks to the guidance of my teachers and seniors.

00:03:33.613 --> 00:03:38.952
Well, I'm not convinced.

00:03:38.952 --> 00:03:41.288
(Kazuki) What?

00:03:41.288 --> 00:03:45.625
When Wate sings solo and Akiyama starts tapping➡

00:03:45.625 --> 00:03:49.496
I feel like everything is being taken away from me.

00:03:49.496 --> 00:03:53.500
Wate's song: It's sung for Akiyama's tap.

00:03:53.500 --> 00:03:58.205
That's right. No one thinks of him that way.

00:03:58.205 --> 00:04:00.574
Is that so?

00:04:00.574 --> 00:04:05.445
Director Hayashi: Are you thinking of letting Wate act as Akiyama's foil?

00:04:05.445 --> 00:04:09.583
I guess you're thinking of making your singing and dancing your two pillars.

00:04:09.583 --> 00:04:12.919
The customers were happy and it was a big hit.

00:04:12.919 --> 00:04:16.590
Sorry, but won't Kazuki have any regrets?

00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:19.493
Before, I was more disappointed.

00:04:19.493 --> 00:04:23.930
Unfortunately, I understand my role now.

00:04:23.930 --> 00:04:27.801
Lily and Akiyama can only shine if we are here.

00:04:27.801 --> 00:04:31.605
See, he's a foil after all!

00:04:31.605 --> 00:04:35.275
Suzuko is really ambitious.

00:04:35.275 --> 00:04:41.148
ambition? You want to stand out even more, right?

00:04:41.148 --> 00:04:47.287
Hmm... I want to stand out➡

00:04:47.287 --> 00:04:50.957
I can't say anything good about it...

00:04:50.957 --> 00:04:55.262
Hona Let me take a picture! (shutter sound)

00:05:00.233 --> 00:05:04.538
Hanayu is as lively as ever.

00:05:09.242 --> 00:05:14.114
(Gonbe) Is this what Yuzu is? (Rokuro) It's like this.

00:05:14.114 --> 00:05:17.117
(Radio) ♬ “Be brave and say you’re going to win.”

00:05:17.117 --> 00:05:20.253
(Umekichi) What a great victory.

00:05:20.253 --> 00:05:23.156
(Gloss) Large. (Umekichi) Japanese Army: There is no enemy on our way.

00:05:23.156 --> 00:05:26.927
(Easy person) Are you going to get this done by New Year's?

00:05:26.927 --> 00:05:29.829
I'm home. (All) Welcome home.

00:05:29.829 --> 00:05:32.799
(Umekichi) Today was good too. It was packed. thank you.

00:05:32.799 --> 00:05:38.271
(Teacher enthusiastically) Sorry, but that tap of Akiyama-chan is already...➡

00:05:38.271 --> 00:05:41.174
That's the best! like this! Let's do this.

00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:45.612
(Asa) I was sure that she would come. (Teacher enthusiastically) Let's go. Yamato II.

00:05:45.612 --> 00:05:49.282
Hmm, but Suzu-chan's singing is a little hazy.

00:05:49.282 --> 00:05:51.218
(Umekichi) Idiot! I'm sick of losing.

00:05:51.218 --> 00:05:54.621
Oh, Suzu-chan won't come either. What would happen if we sang a military song?

00:05:54.621 --> 00:05:56.556
That doesn't suit me.

00:05:56.556 --> 00:05:58.558
I'll get some ramune.

00:06:00.227 --> 00:06:02.162
(Tsuya) What happened?

00:06:02.162 --> 00:06:06.466
Especially... I guess I'm a little tired.

00:06:11.571 --> 00:06:17.444
(Kinu) I'm grateful to Tsuya-chan. ➡

00:06:17.444 --> 00:06:25.585
If things had stayed that way, you and I might not have survived.

00:06:25.585 --> 00:06:35.595
♬～

00:06:35.595 --> 00:06:38.932
(Sound of opening a ramune bottle)

00:06:38.932 --> 00:06:42.269
Here you go.

00:06:42.269 --> 00:06:45.939
thank you. I'll rest in my room for a while.

00:06:45.939 --> 00:06:48.275
Yeah.

00:06:48.275 --> 00:06:50.944
I'm sorry.

00:06:50.944 --> 00:06:55.615
(Radio) ♬ “If you open the window”

00:06:55.615 --> 00:06:58.952
(Umekichi) This song again.

00:06:58.952 --> 00:07:01.855
I've been visiting a lot lately, but I don't like it.

00:07:01.855 --> 00:07:03.790
hang on. What?

00:07:03.790 --> 00:07:06.226
♬ “Meriken Wharf”

00:07:06.226 --> 00:07:10.096
(Easy person) I also don't like this song. It's kind of painful.

00:07:10.096 --> 00:07:14.401
(Umekichi) You say that. (Asa) Yeah, I think it's a good voice.

00:07:16.236 --> 00:07:18.171
Honma...

00:07:18.171 --> 00:07:24.911
♬ “Ride on the love wind”

00:07:24.911 --> 00:07:31.251
undefined

00:07:31.251 --> 00:07:37.924
♬ “Where are you going?”

00:07:37.924 --> 00:07:44.264
"Farewell Blues" Ritsuko Ibarata.

00:07:44.264 --> 00:07:50.971
What... that's a scary face.

00:08:14.561 --> 00:08:19.232
You're thinking too much. Because I can listen to “Farewell Blues”➡

00:08:19.232 --> 00:08:22.569
Why did you break up with me?

00:08:22.569 --> 00:08:28.441
I wonder if that girl knows about Honma...

00:08:28.441 --> 00:08:31.911
What about Honma?

00:08:31.911 --> 00:08:35.582
After that girl came back from Kagawa➡

00:08:35.582 --> 00:08:40.920
I feel like it's a little awkward...

00:08:40.920 --> 00:08:46.226
I care too much. How many years ago, I went to Kagawa.

00:08:47.794 --> 00:08:50.597
He's about his age➡

00:08:50.597 --> 00:08:54.300
I feel like listening to songs I don't understand in the twilight.

00:08:57.937 --> 00:09:01.207
Ah, let's do it! already!

00:09:01.207 --> 00:09:04.110
Here again.

00:09:04.110 --> 00:09:23.897
♬～

00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:25.832
About that one day➡

00:09:25.832 --> 00:09:32.138
Reiko Yamato and Yoshio Matano came to see a performance for the first time in a while.

00:09:37.243 --> 00:09:41.915
(Hat) Eat more and more! Fruit punch!

00:09:41.915 --> 00:09:46.786
With Matano's tearful proposal, the two got married ➡

00:09:46.786 --> 00:09:52.091
My husband and I are currently running dance and piano classes.

00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:57.263
(Yamato) Mr. Fukurai. Ah!

00:09:57.263 --> 00:10:02.936
It was so good! She really liked your song too.

00:10:02.936 --> 00:10:07.273
It gave me strength. thank you very much.

00:10:07.273 --> 00:10:12.145
My stomach has gotten quite big. It's already next month.

00:10:12.145 --> 00:10:16.950
It's more like I said. picture….

00:10:16.950 --> 00:10:20.620
Your song has become a weapon.

00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:24.491
is that so?

00:10:24.491 --> 00:10:29.963
what? what happened? home….

00:10:29.963 --> 00:10:34.834
You think your singing is losing out to Akiyama-san's dancing.

00:10:34.834 --> 00:10:36.836
Nothing like that...

00:10:36.836 --> 00:10:40.974
Akiyama-san said the same thing earlier. picture….

00:10:40.974 --> 00:10:46.312
It seems like my dancing is losing out to your singing.

00:10:46.312 --> 00:10:49.215
Akiyama...

00:10:49.215 --> 00:10:52.652
As always, you guys.

00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:58.658
That's how you improve yourself through friendly competition. I'm jealous.

00:11:01.261 --> 00:11:08.601
It's true that I feel like I'm losing to Akiyama's dance➡

00:11:08.601 --> 00:11:12.272
I don't think that's the case.

00:11:12.272 --> 00:11:17.610
what? I can't say anything nice...➡

00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:22.315
It's not like I want to stand out more than Akiyama...

00:11:23.950 --> 00:11:28.821
What can I say, singing and dancing are fun➡

00:11:28.821 --> 00:11:34.294
There's no such thing...

00:11:34.294 --> 00:11:40.967
I see…. You think she's looking further away.

00:11:40.967 --> 00:11:45.305
Aren't you feeling unsatisfied? To myself now.

00:11:45.305 --> 00:11:48.975
But I don't know what to do.

00:11:48.975 --> 00:11:50.977
That one!

00:11:52.645 --> 00:11:56.516
We don't particularly want to beat Mr. Fukurai's singing or anything.

00:11:56.516 --> 00:11:59.519
I can do more... more...

00:11:59.519 --> 00:12:04.591
That's right! I wonder if she can do more.

00:12:04.591 --> 00:12:06.526
That’s it! That's how I feel!

00:12:06.526 --> 00:12:08.461
(Akiyama) Something like this still doesn't exist...

00:12:08.461 --> 00:12:12.465
Aren't you satisfied? I'm like, "Ah!" …I see!

00:12:12.465 --> 00:12:17.170
You guys are amazing.

00:12:17.170 --> 00:12:20.607
It probably won't be the answer though...➡

00:12:20.607 --> 00:12:26.479
Me, when this child is born➡

00:12:26.479 --> 00:12:29.616
I feel like something about me is about to change.

00:12:29.616 --> 00:12:32.952
That includes dancing and things like that.

00:12:32.952 --> 00:12:38.291
I'm really looking forward to seeing how I change.

00:12:38.291 --> 00:12:44.163
I think that sometimes changes in our lives are reflected in songs and dances.

00:12:44.163 --> 00:12:49.168
Matano-kun, the piano has become softer recently.

00:12:54.307 --> 00:12:57.210
Are you planning on having a baby?

00:12:57.210 --> 00:13:01.914
Ahahahahahaha!

00:13:01.914 --> 00:13:05.785
It's still interesting, Mr. Fukurai.

00:13:05.785 --> 00:13:09.088
Heh heh heh…. different.

00:13:15.928 --> 00:13:21.934
＜Wate tried through trial and error to try to change something about himself＞

00:13:27.273 --> 00:13:30.610
(Lily) Huh! ? Wow! Long eyelashes!

00:13:30.610 --> 00:13:35.281
This one is 2 cm and this one is 3 cm. Which one?

00:13:35.281 --> 00:13:39.952
Hmm, 3 centimeters! Really? Yeah.

00:13:39.952 --> 00:13:44.290
Oh, you guys, just take a look! That's amazing!

00:13:44.290 --> 00:13:46.993
eh! Amazing! Are you going to put that on?

00:13:49.162 --> 00:13:56.169
A visitor from Umemaru's Tokyo branch visited Suzuko's performance.

00:13:57.837 --> 00:14:08.247
♬～

00:14:08.247 --> 00:14:12.585
(Hayashi) Oh! Welcome, Karashima!

00:14:12.585 --> 00:14:16.456
Oh... you haven't changed at all!

00:14:16.456 --> 00:14:21.928
(Karashima) Hello, it's been a long time. Mr. Hayashi hasn't changed at all.

00:14:21.928 --> 00:14:27.600
I drink this every day. Would you like to drink? No, that's fine.

00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:31.270
I'm going to throw up.

00:14:31.270 --> 00:14:35.942
This is a director from Tokyo➡

00:14:35.942 --> 00:14:38.845
Mr. Matsunaga. Matsunaga Zaibatsu...

00:14:38.845 --> 00:14:42.615
Nice to meet you, I'm Matsunaga. Good luck.

00:14:42.615 --> 00:14:47.954
(Hayashi) Please listen to me. You studied abroad in Paris and London, right?

00:14:47.954 --> 00:14:51.624
ah. Well, it's a world tour. ah! Please do!

00:14:51.624 --> 00:14:55.328
I just returned and I'm not familiar with Japanese. sorry.

